l-cooking-stream\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"'${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks/run-hook.cmd' session-start\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"635e933c-26cf-4145-9532-fd1963bb1a07\",\"toolUseID\":\"635e933c-26cf-4145-9532-fd1963bb1a07\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T23:18:57.482Z\",\"uuid\":\"cc0736c2-f8c7-409f-af71-d3ddb2e5c3aa\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"cc0736c2-f8c7-409f-af71-d3ddb2e5c3aa\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"23bbbe0f-ba88-46ac-858f-c442a33310d7\",\"version\":\"2.1.59\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/fix-failing-gemini-e2e\",\"slug\":\"magical-cooking-stream\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Fix: Context compaction resets CheckpointTranscriptStart causing stale carry-forward\\n\\n## Context\\n\\n`TestRapidSequentialCommits` fails for Gemini because context compaction events (`pre-compress` hooks) unconditionally reset `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0` in `lifecycle.go:410`. The Gemini transcript file grows monotonically (never truncated during compaction), so this reset causes stale files to re-appear in carry-forward.\\n\\n### Why the reset is wrong\\n\\nGemini CLI fires `pre-compress` after **every tool call** as part of its standard `after-tool → pre-compress → before-model` pipeline. The E2E logs show it firing 8 times (once per tool call) with only ~10K tokens. The transcript file shows zero evidence of actual compression: all 9 messages are intact, no lines removed, no compaction summary entry inserted. These `pre-compress` events are **no-ops** transcript-wise.\\n\\nThe handler unconditionally resets `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0` on every `pre-compress`, even when no compression actually occurred. This causes subsequent `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript` calls to re-scan already-condensed messages.\\n\\n### Failure timeline (from `entire.log` and transcript)\\n\\nTranscript: 9 messages — msg 2: `write_file red.md`, msg 4: `write_file blue.md`, msg 6: `write_file green.md`.\\n\\n1. **Commit 1 (red.md)**: `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript(offset=0)` → `[\\\"docs/red.md\\\"]`. Condensation → `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 3`\\n2. **Compaction (`pre-compress`)**: resets `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0`\\n3. **Commit 2 (blue.md)**: `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript(offset=0)` re-scans ALL msgs → `[\\\"docs/red.md\\\",\\\"docs/blue.md\\\"]`. `subtractFilesByName` removes blue → carry-forward `[\\\"red.md\\\"]`\\n4. **Commit 3 (green.md)**: `FilesTouched = [\\\"docs/red.md\\\"]`, committed=`{\\\"docs/green.md\\\"}` → no overlap → `should_condense: false` → shadow branch persists → **test fails**\\n\\n## Fix\\n\\n### 1. Remove unconditional transcript offset reset in compaction handler\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go:410`\\n\\nRemove:\\n```go\\nsessionState.CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0\\n```\\n\\nAlso update the stderr message to remove \\\"transcript offset reset\\\".\\n\\nIn this test, `pre-compress` fires as a no-op — no actual compression occurs, so the offset should not be reset. We have no evidence of what a *real* Gemini compaction would do to the on-disk transcript (truncate, insert summary, etc.).\\n\\nRemoving the reset is safe because:\\n- For no-op compactions (the observed case): offset remains correct\\n- For real compactions that might alter the transcript: `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset` handles offset > length gracefully (returns empty — the loop simply doesn't iterate), which is a safe default since those files were already condensed\\n- If we later discover real compactions need special handling, we can add agent-specific logic at that point\\n\\n### 2. Update existing compaction test\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle_test.go`\\n\\nThe existing test `TestHandleLifecycleCompaction_ResetsTranscriptOffset` explicitly verifies the reset behavior. Update it to verify the offset is **preserved** instead.\\n\\n### 3. Add a unit test for the carry-forward scenario\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks_test.go` (or `manual_commit_test.go`)\\n\\nAdd a test that simulates the bug scenario: after condensation sets `CheckpointTranscriptStart = N`, verify that `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript` only returns files after offset N (not from offset 0).\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci` — all tests pass\\n2. Run the failing E2E test: `mise run test:e2e:gemini TestRapidSequentialCommits`\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alex/.claude/projects/-Users-alex-workspace-cli--worktrees-1/8b761911-336c-4f6c-9756-df16fb765955.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"6a007b6a-46e0-4a02-a32d-8457dd668e76\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T23:18:57.020Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Fix: Context compaction resets CheckpointTranscriptStart causing stale carry-forward\\n\\n## Context\\n\\n`TestRapidSequentialCommits` fails for Gemini because context compaction events (`pre-compress` hooks) unconditionally reset `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0` in `lifecycle.go:410`. The Gemini transcript file grows monotonically (never truncated during compaction), so this reset causes stale files to re-appear in carry-forward.\\n\\n### Why the reset is wrong\\n\\nGemini CLI fires `pre-compress` after **every tool call** as part of its standard `after-tool → pre-compress → before-model` pipeline. The E2E logs show it firing 8 times (once per tool call) with only ~10K tokens. The transcript file shows zero evidence of actual compression: all 9 messages are intact, no lines removed, no compaction summary entry inserted. These `pre-compress` events are **no-ops** transcript-wise.\\n\\nThe handler unconditionally resets `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0` on every `pre-compress`, even when no compression actually occurred. This causes subsequent `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript` calls to re-scan already-condensed messages.\\n\\n### Failure timeline (from `entire.log` and transcript)\\n\\nTranscript: 9 messages — msg 2: `write_file red.md`, msg 4: `write_file blue.md`, msg 6: `write_file green.md`.\\n\\n1. **Commit 1 (red.md)**: `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript(offset=0)` → `[\\\"docs/red.md\\\"]`. Condensation → `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 3`\\n2. **Compaction (`pre-compress`)**: resets `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0`\\n3. **Commit 2 (blue.md)**: `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript(offset=0)` re-scans ALL msgs → `[\\\"docs/red.md\\\",\\\"docs/blue.md\\\"]`. `subtractFilesByName` removes blue → carry-forward `[\\\"red.md\\\"]`\\n4. **Commit 3 (green.md)**: `FilesTouched = [\\\"docs/red.md\\\"]`, committed=`{\\\"docs/green.md\\\"}` → no overlap → `should_condense: false` → shadow branch persists → **test fails**\\n\\n## Fix\\n\\n### 1. Remove unconditional transcript offset reset in compaction handler\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go:410`\\n\\nRemove:\\n```go\\nsessionState.CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0\\n```\\n\\nAlso update the stderr message to remove \\\"transcript offset reset\\\".\\n\\nIn this test, `pre-compress` fires as a no-op — no actual compression occurs, so the offset should not be reset. We have no evidence of what a *real* Gemini compaction would do to the on-disk transcript (truncate, insert summary, etc.).\\n\\nRemoving the reset is safe because:\\n- For no-op compactions (the observed case): offset remains correct\\n- For real compactions that might alter the transcript: `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset` handles offset > length gracefully (returns empty — the loop simply doesn't iterate), which is a safe default since those files were already condensed\\n- If we later discover real compactions need special handling, we can add agent-specific logic at that point\\n\\n### 2. Update existing compaction test\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle_test.go`\\n\\nThe existing test `TestHandleLifecycleCompaction_ResetsTranscriptOffset` explicitly verifies the reset behavior. Update it to verify the offset is **preserved** instead.\\n\\n### 3. Add a unit test for the carry-forward scenario\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks_test.go` (or `manual_commit_test.go`)\\n\\nAdd a test that simulates the bug scenario: after condensation sets `CheckpointTranscriptStart = N`, verify that `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript` only returns files after offset N (not from offset 0).\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci` — all tests pass\\n2. Run the failing E2E test: `mise run test:e2e:gemini TestRapidSequentialCommits`\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"6a007b6a-46e0-4a02-a32d-8457dd668e76\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"23bbbe0f-ba88-46ac-858f-c442a33310d7\",\"version\":\"2.1.59\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/fix-failing-gemini-e2e\",\"slug\":\"magical-cooking-stream\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_017vg2vdDT6trJtFGSVJ6K4e\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\nI'll implement this fix. Let me start by reading the relevant files.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":48280,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":11043,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":48280},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYXY2rpEoXx8zMYQvsyvp\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"4d71d793-19d6-4b62-82eb-7ca452d90e77\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T23:19:01.481Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"4d71d793-19d6-4b62-82eb-7ca452d90e77\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"23bbbe0f-ba88-46ac-858f-c442a33310d7\",